Copyright statement of the author of the image

イラストの転載・使用に関するレギュレーションです▼

作品に関しては、「他作品等への提供物ではないもの・オリジナル作品」は転載（SNSや掲示板への掲載等）を許可します（趣味イラストなど）（常識的な範囲内での転載行為は許可してるので、メッセージでのご連絡などは無くても大丈夫です）　

ただし「二次創作作品」の転載や、作品の商用利用、に関しては連絡をください

創作（動画等）の使用に関しては、作品の設定を壊さない程度であれば使用を許可しております（音楽動画のサムネなど）

ただし、作品に対し設定を加えた上での使用（シチュエーションボイス動画等）に関しては、設定の変化や勝手な付加が起こって欲しくないため、無断での使用は禁止しております　もしどうしてもそのような使用をしたい場合、使いたい絵と、それに対し加えたい設定やシチュエーションをセットでご相談いただければ検討いたします

個人的な範囲での使用（PCやスマホの壁紙　ＳＮＳのアイコンやヘッダー画像など）に関しては、改変しなければ自由に許可しております

動画などの創作や個人的な所有物に対する絵の使用は「転載」ではなく「作品の使用」に値するという認識です

ただし、誹謗中傷や作者偽りなどの目的での転載や、pixivのようなイラストサイトへの投稿という形での転載は禁止します　絵の指摘だったらその絵のコメント欄とかでしてくだされば嬉しいな！

Description

Model

recommand base model: counterfeitV25

lora recommand: about 0.7

The model is good at expressing light, and at this point it learns well from the original artist. But it does poorly on night scenes. If you use the promt of the picture example I posted, the random seed usually performs well. It may not perform well when you use more detailed descriptors.

The training of this model is done at a resolution of 1024*1024, I strongly recommend you use a resolution of around 768 for painting.

When the weight of lora increases, the picture will be destroyed, and the eyes of the characters will become ugly.

This is an overfitting model, and too many promts will also cause the screen to collapse.

I've been working on the 3090 for over a week and it still can't perfectly replicate the artist's beautiful style. I'm sorry but I did my best.

Trianing

I tried using Loha, but the model struggled to converge and the anatomy of the characters was very poorly broken. I have tried the following parameters (linear layer alpha = 1, convolutional layer alpha = 1):

  • linear layer dim = 128, convolutional layer dim = 32

  • linear layer dim = 64, convolutional layer dim = 32

  • linear layer alpha = 64, convolutional layer alpha = 16

  • linear layer alpha = 64, convolutional layer alpha = 8

  • linear layer alpha = 32, convolutional layer alpha = 16

I also tried using Locon, but I experimented with less parameter combinations.

Every training is tens of thousands of steps.

I think loha doesn't perform well in the training of painting styles that are not obvious.

This released version lora dim = 128.

I also tried dim=192 and I don't think there is a noticeable difference in their performance.

Regularization

When the regularization weight is 1, 0.5, 0.25, 0.125, it is difficult for the model to converge. In fact, 0.08 and 0.05 also converge slowly, but 0.05 still has an overfitting problem.

Dataset

image429077: 133 img & txt

image429077hasreg: each img in separate folder, good for regularization

reg: reg_all

You can make 133 images correspond to 2000 regularized images. It is also possible to have each image correspond to a separate regularized image, which is generated using the promt obtained by the corresponding inversion.


If you want to use the overall regularized image, please use the python file in my compressed package and change the source image directory and target directory.

Integrating helps to get a consistent style, training separately helps to get interesting results.

items.name: 【Characters】KDA Series (All-in-One)
items.description:
2023/4/6 update

Upload Lycoris version. v1.0 version is conventional LoRA model.

Introduction

A conventional LoRA model of KDA Series, including 4 characters, Ahri, Akali, Evelynn and Kai'sa. 0.6~0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.6 version (original) YesMix.

Usage

The universal trigger tag is 'k/da \(league of legends\)'.

  • For Ahri, the trigger tag is 'ahri \(league of legends\)'. The key features are 'fox girl, fox ears, fox tail, blonde hair, choker, facial mark, whisker markings'.

  • For Akali, the trigger tag is 'akali'. The key features are 'baseball cap, choker, cropped jacket, ponytail, mask (optional), kunai (optional)'.

  • For Evelynn, the trigger tag is 'evelynn \(league of legends\)'. The key features are 'choker, crop top, feather trim, midriff, hair between eyes, purple hair, claws, sunglasses (optional)'.

  • For Kai'sa, the trigger tag is 'kai'sa'. The key features are 'choker, double bun, hair bun'.

See the preview images for details. Btw, this model is trained with some images that contain the baddest outfits and prestige outfits. Therefore, images that contain the above outfits can be also generated using this model, theoretically.

Cautions (Must Read)

  • Some preview images are generated using hires fix. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

  • The maximum of generating resolution should not exceed 1024 theoretically, otherwise extra/deformed head/limbs will be waiting for you :). Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: SR-Alpha
items.description:
SR-Alpha aims to combine comic art style with semi-realistic textures.

I highly recommend inpainting for best results and to unlock the full potential of the merge. Separate inpainting model not required.

To help with inpainting human features, I have also been tinkering with this extension called !After Detailer, which automatically detects and "fixes" the portion of the image being generated via txt2img depending on the "ADetailer" model used, notably the models for the hands and face which I use most often.

PS:
As I have not updated this merge in quite a long time, I no longer remember the exact models used for versions 1-1.2. I believe that with the new update, the old versions would be rendered obsolete.

V2 Mix Recipe:

  • helloComic_v10Beta

  • OccidentalMix - v2.0

  • fazz - v1.0

Recommended Settings:

V 1.0:

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Sampling Steps: 50

V1.1 and above:

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ 2M Karras, Euler A (Inpainting)

  • Sampling Steps: 30

CFG = 7-10

Denoising Strength = 0.3-0.5 (img2img/inpainting)

Suggested Embeddings:

  • https://civitai.com/models/17083/bad-picture-negative-embedding-for-chilloutmix

  • https://civitai.com/models/11772/verybadimagenegative

  • https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1032948846197747731/1069660323709190195/bad-hands-5.pt

  • Deep Negative V1.x - V1 75T | Stable Diffusion Textual Inversion | Civitai

  • Bad artist Negative embedding - Bad artist | Stable Diffusion Textual Inversion | Civitai

VAE:

  • NoCrypt/blessed_vae · Hugging Face

Credits to the respective original creators of the resources used.

items.name: IPoser1.7.1
items.description:
这是一个使用unity开发的人物姿势图片生成工具，可以独立运行，并生成png格式姿势图。

功能说明：

可以直接点击肢体，用Gizmo调整肢体角度或人整体位置

可以改变人姿势的姿势，也可以移动人体位置

可以在运行时修改分辨率

可以生成多人姿势

可以保存和载入姿势数据

基本操作说明：

1.界面：

•左下角的"Screen Shot"按钮，是截屏功能，调整好姿势和视角后，可以点击这个按钮截图，截图目录在 IPoserV1.7.1\IPoser V1.71_Data

•右上角面板的"R"按钮，是当前所选人体所有组件角度复位功能

•右下角的"Reset"按钮，是所有人体的所有组件角度复位功能

•右下角的"AddPoser"按钮，是增加一个人体功能

•右下角的"Delete"按钮，是删除被选中的人体的功能（第一个人体无法被删除）

•左"Scr"按钮，是分辨率设置功能界面

•左"Single"按钮，是肢体选择模式切换功能，分别是整体旋转和平衡(whole body)和肢体旋转(Single Limb)两个选项，前者可以旋转和移动，后者只能旋转

•左"GetAndOut"按钮，是姿势数据保存和输入功能界面：

保存数据：先选择人物（出现Gizmo图标），点"Get"按钮，左边的窗口中就会显示出当前选择的这个人的所有姿势数据，可以直接COPY，然后另存。

输入数据：在“Enter Current Poser's data”窗口中粘贴入姿势数据，再选择人物（出现Gizmo图标），点击"Enter"按钮，被选中的人物就会成为数据中的姿势。

2.鼠标操作：

•左键点击人体，可以选取人体组件

•右键按住移动鼠标，可以旋转镜头角度

•(如果有中间滚轮），转动滚轮，可以缩放画面

•(如果有中键或中间滚轮可以被按下）,按下后，移动鼠标可以移动镜头中心点位置

~~~~~~~~~~English~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

This is a tool for generating character pose images developed using Unity, which can run independently and generate pose images in PNG format.

Functional description:

- Clicking on a limb allows you to adjust the angle of the limb or the position of the entire person using the Gizmo.

- You can change the posture of the person and also move their position.

- You can modify the resolution during runtime.

- You can generate poses with multiple people.

- You can save and load pose data.

Basic operation instructions:

1. Interface:

- The "Screen Shot" button at the bottom left corner is for taking screenshots. After adjusting the pose and viewing angle, click this button to take a screenshot. The screenshot directory is in IPoserV1.7.1\IPoser V1.71_Data.

- The "R" button in the top right panel is for resetting the angles of all components of the selected person.

- The "Reset" button in the bottom right corner resets the angles of all components of all characters.

- The "AddPoser" button in the bottom right corner is for adding a new character.

- The "Delete" button in the bottom right corner is for deleting the selected person (the first person cannot be deleted).

- The "Scr" button on the left side is for resolution settings.

- The "Single" button on the left side is for switching between limb selection modes. There are two options: "whole body" and "single limb". The former allows rotation and movement, while the latter only allows rotation.

- The "GetAndOut" button on the left side is for pose data saving and input:

Save data: select the character (Gizmo icon appears), click the "Get" button, and the left window will display all the pose data for the currently selected character. You can directly COPY and then save it.

Input data: paste the pose data into the "Enter Current Poser's data" window, select the character (Gizmo icon appears), and click the "Enter" button. The selected character will become the pose in the data.

2. Mouse operations:

- Left-clicking on a person selects their components.

- Holding down the right mouse button and moving the mouse can rotate the camera angle.

- (If there is a scroll wheel) rotating the scroll wheel can zoom in or out of the screen.

- (If there is a middle button or scroll wheel that can be pressed) Pressing it and moving the mouse can move the camera center point.

This is a tool for generating character pose images developed using Unity, which can run independently and generate pose images in PNG format.

保存数据：先选择人物（出现Gizmo图标），点"Get"按钮，左边的窗口中就会显示出当前选择的这个人的所有姿势数据，可以直接COPY，然后另存。

输入数据：在“Enter Current Poser's data”窗口中粘贴入姿势数据，再选择人物（出现Gizmo图标），点击"Enter"按钮，被选中的人物就会成为数据中的姿势。

2.鼠标操作：

•左键点击人体，可以选取人体组件

•右键按住移动鼠标，可以旋转镜头角度

•(如果有中间滚轮），转动滚轮，可以缩放画面

•(如果有中键或中间滚轮可以被按下）,按下后，移动鼠标可以移动镜头中心点位置

~~~~~~~~~~English~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

v1.7.1

Functional description:

- Clicking on a limb allows you to adjust the angle of the limb or the position of the entire person using the Gizmo.

- You can change the posture of the person and also move their position.

- You can modify the resolution during runtime.

- You can generate poses with multiple people.

- You can save and load pose data.

Basic operation instructions:

1. Interface:

- The "Screen Shot" button at the bottom left corner is for taking screenshots. After adjusting the pose and viewing angle, click this button to take a screenshot. The screenshot directory is in IPoserV1.7.1\IPoser V1.71_Data.

- The "R" button in the top right panel is for resetting the angles of all components of the selected person.

- The "Reset" button in the bottom right corner resets the angles of all components of all characters.

- The "AddPoser" button in the bottom right corner is for adding a new character.

- The "Delete" button in the bottom right corner is for deleting the selected person (the first person cannot be deleted).

- The "Scr" button on the left side is for resolution settings.

- The "Single" button on the left side is for switching between limb selection modes. There are two options: "whole body" and "single limb". The former allows rotation and movement, while the latter only allows rotation.

- The "GetAndOut" button on the left side is for pose data saving and input:

Save data: select the character (Gizmo icon appears), click the "Get" button, and the left window will display all the pose data for the currently selected character. You can directly COPY and then save it.

Input data: paste the pose data into the "Enter Current Poser's data" window, select the character (Gizmo icon appears), and click the "Enter" button. The selected character will become the pose in the data.

2. Mouse operations:

- Left-clicking on a person selects their components.

- Holding down the right mouse button and moving the mouse can rotate the camera angle.

- (If there is a scroll wheel) rotating the scroll wheel can zoom in or out of the screen.

- (If there is a middle button or scroll wheel that can be pressed) Pressing it and moving the mouse can move the camera center point.

  • Regular kimono - ryougi shiki, obi, blue kimono, boots (it's basically her regular outfit without jacket)

  • Red kimono - ryougi shiki, sash, red kimono, obijime

  • Casual ( ͡° ͜ʖ ͡°) - ryougi shiki, white shirt, white panties, barefoot, no pants

  • White kimono - ryougi shiki, obi, white kimono, obijime, floral print (also FGO first ascension)

items.name: Aayla Secura | Star Wars
items.description:
Aayla Secura | Star Wars

This is my first LoRA. Feel free to leave some feedback and ideas for improvement.

Genereal training information

Based on 30 images cropped to 768 x 768.

Manually refined the captions from BLIP afterwards.

Run with 100 steps per image totals in 3000 steps.

Trained on SD1.5

GTX1080 ~ 4h

I did some basic testing, the following settings can be tried out as a baseline:

  • Model: SD1.5, however, other models are working well too (Mostly tested with The Ally's Mix)

  • CFG: 6-9, mostly used 7

  • Steps: 22, 30, 35 worked well with 2M Karras and DDIM

  • 768 by 768 will probably yield best results as it was trained on this dimensions

  • LoRA weight: 0.3 [very far away from real Aayla but works sometimes]; 0.6 [very nice middleground for getting some batches for testing]; 0.8 [also worked very nice]; 0.9 [wouldn't go higher as the results turn out weirdly]

Styles

  • Realistic: (ultra realistic:1.1) [example image 1 and 2]

  • Cartoon: (cartoon:1.2) [weight 1.5 really exaggerates the cartoon look, therfore face details have to be sacrificed; example image 3, 4 with latent upscaling]

  • Drawing: drawing:1.1 of [pretty similar to cartoon, I personally facor cartoon]

Promts that should trigger additional training data:

  • wearing star wars costume

  • wearing star wars outfit

  • leather headpiece

  • blue light saber (put this on the negative promts if you don't want blue lights everywhere)

*most example images where upscaled with denoising around 0.55 (2 times, latent)

items.name: Mistoon_Emerald
items.description:
You can now get all my LoRAs in one single package if you subscribe to my Patreon (including those not on CivitAI):

The Complete Catalog Download | Patreon

What's new in V2?

Emerald is my least downloaded checkpoint and personal least favorite. It was too focused on a single style, and all the characters were really similar to each other. For V2 I've rebuilt the dataset from scratch using a custom LoRA trained on the pictures I liked from the previous iteration and adding an unreleased LoRA to make it more vibrant. The result is a more flexible model with less over saturated colors and easier to use with higher CFG values.

How to use this

If you are new to the world of Stable Diffusion, you can learn how to run it by yourself here:

Tutorial

You'll also need a VAE to use this. For the examples, I've used the Grapefruit one:

https://huggingface.co/iZELX1/Grapefruit/resolve/main/Grapefruit.vae.pt

What's this model

Mistoon_Emerald is a variant of my SD model Mistoon_Anime that tries to achieve a more "fan art cartoon" style while still maintaining some resemblance to the modern anime style.

The starting point for this model was my blend. From there, I then added a few of my custom LoRAs in the mix to change the esthetic.

Try also the other flavors:

The style

It creates realistic and expressive characters with a "cartoony" twist. Unlike other anime models that tend to have muted or dark colors, Mistoon_Emerald uses bright and vibrant colors to make the characters stand out.

All the examples have been created using this version of the model using my workflow. Check the guide if you want to learn more about my workflow.

The model can also easily do NSFW stuff (check the last examples).

I highly suggest using a low CFG (3-5) value to avoid the usual burn effect.

Guides

Learn how to create pictures like mine with my step-by-step tutorials:

items.name: Austin Theory
items.description:
Well, let me tell you about Austin Theory from WWE. This rising superstar is like a magnet for attention, and his charisma is off the charts. He's like a firework exploding in the night sky - impossible to ignore and impossible to forget.

But let's talk about his features - those beautiful blue eyes that sparkle like diamonds in the ring, and those big, luscious lips that seem like they were made for a god. They're so mesmerizing that they inspired an entire LoRA training session, and now every LoRA library needs a snack like Austin Theory to keep the creativity and other juices flowing.

Just a heads up that the LoRA has been trained on both old and new photos of Theory, including ones where he has a beard

If you want to generate an image of him without the beard, you can simply specify that in the negative prompt.

items.name: Agnieszka Dygant
items.description:
This is my first LyCORIS.

I believe that the LyCORIS quality is superior to that of a regular LORA.

In general, my technique has not changed. I still train a dreambooth model and then extract the result. Previously I've been extracting it as a LORA, now it will be a LyCORIS.

I still keep all the trained Dreambooths but I feel like it is no longer necessary to upload them as the LyCORIS quality is "good enough".

Samples were done on various models. You need to test the weight on each model as different checkpoint actually prefers different weights.

RealisticVision tends to work with 1.0 (probably because that was the base of the dreambooth training) but others need between 0.8 and 1.4 usually.

Realistic models will give us realistic outputs, stylized models will give us stylized results :)
